
Philippine Defense Secretary Gilberto Teodoro was chosen by the ruling coalition
Lakas-Kampi- CMD as its candidate to join the 2010 presidential election race,
the coalition announced Wednesday.

Teodoro, 45, won by a landslide against Metropolitan Manila Development
Authority chair Bayani Fernando as 52 of the 64-member Lakas-Kampi-CMD execute
committee convened Wednesday in a downtown Manila hotel.

Making the announcement, coalition party secretary-general Gabriel Claudio said
that the two were both worthy presidential aspirants but in the end one man
alone had to be chosen.

Claudio said Teodoro's selection is subject to the ratification by the coalition
party's national convention, the national TV network GMA News reported.
